** Job Title : Senior Machine Learning Engineer **

Replica Studios are at the forefront of the AI voice industry at the
intersection of AI x gaming. They are constantly pushing boundaries and
innovating in the field of ethical AI voice synthesis.

They are on the lookout for Machine Learning Engineers to join their team
(remotely or at their office).

** To succeed in this role, you will need: **

  * Strong programming ability. Experience in Python is preferred. 
  * Experience implementing Machine Learning and Deep Learning models. 
  * Experience implementing research papers, running GitHub repos, or open source models. 
  * Ability to work on both open-ended research problems and production-ready code. 
  * Ability to work autonomously when required, and to take initiative with research activities and ensure that this research model is integrated with the product. 
  * Look into details and take ownership of work all the way from research to production 
  * Enthusiasm for games and artificial intelligence. 
  * Detail oriented thinking and time management. 
  * Excellent collaboration and communication skills. 

  
** What to expect / Benefits Include **

  * Opportunity to participate in the growth phase of an AI company that is building cutting-edge voice AI software for the world's leading game engines and blockbuster studios. 
  * Solve exciting and challenging problems that could power the next generation of video games. 
  * Be part of a world leading team that values initiative, flexibility, and imagination 
  * A remote and flexible working arrangement around core operational hours. 
  * Multiple cross functional growth & development opportunities as the team grows (tech / mentoring / management / customer facing). 

  
